cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SD, cs.NI 

The paper deals with the analysis of high-dimensional data using geometrical space embedding, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). The focus on network geometry and hyperbolic space suggests a possible fit with the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and statistical learning (cs.SD). Finally, the use of a new index to quantify the separation of data clusters suggests a possible fit with the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NI).
